This paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms for the classification of RNA-seq expression data, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of RNA-seq expression data also suggests a potential overlap with computer vision (cs.CV) and database (cs.DB) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the need for accurate methods for cancer diagnosis, which could potentially fall under the computational biology (cs.CE) sub-category.
